description:
This option once is used when configurate active/passive cluster. If you set Cluster.mode to passive_legacy, on the standby server, set
                      FolderMonitor.enable and Scheduler.enable to false. When you remove a server from an active/passive cluster, the result is two stand-alone
                      servers. Then you must set FolderMonitor.enable and Scheduler.enable to true. When the primary server fails in an active/passive cluster with cluster mode set to
                      passive_legacy, you must perform a manual failover on the passive standby server. To do this, set both FolderMonitor.enable and Scheduler.enable to true. Note: This parameter is supported by Standard cluster only.
name: Scheduler.enable

description:
Specifies a timeout that determines how long a secondary server waits before
                      declaring itself the primary server. The default value is 60000 milliseconds. This parameter is supported for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.connectionTimeout

description: Specifies the local certificate alias to be used when encrypting cluster communication. Note: This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.Crypto.Alias

description:
Specifies the current cluster deployment site. This option is supported only for EC and requires TM restart when changed. Possible values: < Prod | DR > 
                      "Prod" is used for Production Site, "DR" - for Disaster Recovery Site. Set Cluster.EnableDRConfiguration to true in order to specify the Production and DR nodes.
name: Cluster.DeploymentSite

description: SSL protocol used for dynamic synchronization. Allowed options are: TLSv1 | TLSv1.1 | TLSv1.2 | TLSv1.3. If no option is specified, the default value of TLSv1.3 will be used.
name: Cluster.DynamicSync.SSLProtocol

description: Specifies whether cluster communication should be encrypted. This parameter is supported only for Enterprise Cluster. Requires Admin and TM services restart when changed.
name: Cluster.enable.SSL

description: Specifies whether Disaster Recovery settings can be configured. Possible values: < true | false > This option is supported only for EC
name: Cluster.EnableDRConfiguration

description: Configures the name and location of the cluster_state file. The location is relative to Cluster.File.clusterStateFile.relative. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.File.clusterStateFile.path

description: Configures the location of the cluster_state file. See also Cluster.File.clusterStateFile.path. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.File.clusterStateFile.relative

description: The default path to sentinel_file is /var/tmp/sentinel_primary. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.File.sentinelFile.path

description: This is the ST installation home directory. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.File.sentinelFile.relative

description: The default group name is STCluster.
name: Cluster.groupname

description: Number of credits for FC protocol in Standard cluster.
name: Cluster.InitialFCredits

description: Enable SSL listener for cluster. The default value is true which means it's enabled by default. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.Listeners.Listener.enable.SSL

description: Defines the port for SSL listener. The default value is 44431. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.Listeners.Listener.port.SSL

description: Enabled cipher suites used to set up secure connection for inter-node communication in Standard cluster. The default value is TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.

description: The ssl key algorithm used. The default value is SunX509. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.Listeners.Ssl.keyAlgorithm

description: The ssl protocol used. The default value is TLSv1.3. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.Listeners.Ssl.protocol

description: The timeout to wait for merge. The default timeout is 60000. Supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.mergeTimeout

description: The default message processing poll interval is 10. Supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.messageProcessingPollInterval

description: Possible cluster mode values: disabled (if clustering is disabled); active (if Active-Active clustering); passive (if Active-Passive clustering); passive_legacy (if Active-Passive legacy mode). Supported only for Standard Cluster.
name: Cluster.mode

description: Rule for number of online nodes threshold. Supported only for Enterprise Cluster (EC).

Once the Monitor server stops attempting to restart a service, you must restart it manually. This parameter is supported only for Standard Cluster.

description: When transferring files over PeSIT protocol in ASCII mode, SecureTransport counts the number of characters on each line and stores them in memory. When transfer is finished, this data is stored on the file system. This parameter limits the number of line counters stored in memory (each "counter is 4 bytes) before the data gets flushed to file. Increasing this parameter can improve performance but will increase the memory usage by the TM and the PeSIT daemon. Allowed values are greater or equal to 1024. The default value is 32768.

description:
Reflects your input in the Group ID Attribute text box under
                     User Attributes Names in Authentication > SiteMinder Settings.
                     When the "Explicitly uses SiteMinder Attributes" checkbox is set to true,
                     SecureTransport uses this value to determine the SiteMinder users group ID (GID).
                     For SiteMinder users mapped as SecureTransport virtual users, this value is ignored.
name: Siteminder.UserAttributesMap.gidAttr

description:
Reflects your input in the Home Folder Attribute text box under
                     User Attributes Names in Authentication > SiteMinder Settings.
                     When the "Explicitly uses SiteMinder Attributes" checkbox is set to true,
                     SecureTransport uses this value to determine the SiteMinder users home folder.
                     For SiteMinder users mapped as SecureTransport virtual users, this value is ignored.
name: Siteminder.UserAttributesMap.homeDirAttr

description:
Defines if SecureTransport should use SiteMinder user attributes as specified under either
                     User Attribute Names or Default User Properties in "SiteMinder Settings".
                     Reflects the selection of the "Explicitly uses SiteMinder Attributes" checkbox in
                     Authentication > SiteMinder Settings: true when selected, false when cleared.
                     When true, SecureTransport uses your input in the following SiteMinder settings under
                     User Attribute Names: Home folder, User ID, and Group ID.
                     When false, SecureTransport uses your input in the following SiteMinder settings under
                     Default User Properties: Default Home folder, Default User ID and Default Group ID with
                     SiteMinder external accounts.
name: Siteminder.UserAttributesMap.homeDirAttr.forced

description:

description:
Streaming.LoadBalancingPolicy defines the algorithm for choosing the connection between the protocol daemon and Transaction Managers that will handle the client generated traffic.  
                      The connection is chosen when the client establishes a session and it is used for the lifespan of the user session. Valid values are: Blacklist-Round-Robin, Round-Robin, Blacklist-Random and Random. 
                      If the value is set to Round-Robin, first the Transaction Manager is chosen in circular order and then its least used connection is utilized. 
                      If the value is set to Random, a random connection from the list of all available connections is utilized.
                      Blacklist-Round-Robin and Blacklist-Random work exactly the same way as Round-Robin and Random, but add a filtering of bad connections.
                      The default and recommended value is Blacklist-Round-Robin.
name: Streaming.LoadBalancingPolicy

description: Defines the default path attribute for the homeDir alias in case it's not defined from the user.
name: Users.Defaults.Directory.homeDir.path

description: Defines the default relative attribute in case it's not defined from the user.
name: Users.Defaults.Directory.homeDir.relative

description: The default GID is 2000.
name: Users.Defaults.gid

description: The default UID is 10000.
name: Users.Defaults.uid

description: Number of failed ssh key login attempts to lock user accounts. Value can be any non-negative number, where 0 means never. Values of other types will be ignored and default value will be used instead. The default value is 100.
name: Users.DefaultSshKeyLockoutLimit

description: The SecureTransport Server is compliant with the SFTP protocol specification and does not apply a umask to the mode bits if they are specified by the client. If the mode bits are not specified by the client, the umask is applied based on the configuration of this option. If no value is set, the operating system's umask is used.
name: Users.DefaultUmask

description: Deny access for certain groups.
name: Users.DeniedGroups

description: Deny access for certain users.
name: Users.DeniedUsers

description: Download restrictions dnloads <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Downloads

description: User limits <class> <n> <times> [<msg file>].
name: Users.Limits

description: It specifies bandwidth limit in kb/s for HTTP/FTP/SSH inbound transfers. You can edit it from Setup->Miscellaneous.
name: Users.Limits.Bandwidth.Inbound

description: It specifies bandwidth limit in kb/s for HTTP/FTP/SSH outbound transfers. You can edit it from Setup->Miscellaneous.
name: Users.Limits.Bandwidth.Outbound

description: It specifies a throttling timeout for all transfers that are with limited bandwidth.
name: Users.Limits.Bandwidth.Throttling.Timeout

description: Messages displayed to FTP users when limit is enforced.
name: Users.Limits.Messages

description:
Controls the conversion of user names entered during login. Valid values are:
                      - lower  The user name is converted by mapping all alphabetic character to
                      lower case. This is the default.
                      -upper  The user name is converted by mapping all alphabetic character to
                      upper case.
                      -none  The user name is not converted.
name: Users.LoginNames.normalizedCaseInsensitiveUsername

description: Controls whether the user name of a virtual user is case sensitive. <true|false>.
name: Users.LoginNames.virtualUserCaseSensitive

description: Control file system restrictions - all access to file/directory <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.All

description: Control file system restrictions - chmod <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Chmod

description: Control file system restrictions - delete <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Delete

description: Control file system restrictions - mkdir <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Mkdir

description: Control file system restrictions - overwrite <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Overwrite

description: Control file system restrictions - rename <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Rename

description: Control file system restrictions - rmdir <yes|no> <class> <path>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Rmdir

description: Control file system restrictions - umask <yes|no> <class>.
name: Users.Restrictions.Umask

description:
Minimum number of characters for secret answer. Default value is 0 which means no restrictions are
            in place. Setting the option to anything but a positive number will set it to its default value.
name: Users.SecretAnswer.MinLength

description: Global enable or disable secret question feature.
name: Users.SecretQuestion.Enabled

description: Allowed attempts for guessing the answer before locking the account.
name: Users.SecretQuestion.MaxAttempts

description: Specifies whether a secret question is required for password reset.
name: Users.SecretQuestion.Required

description: List with secret questions.
name: Users.SecretQuestions

description: Controls the status of users client certificate ssh authentication <none|optional|required>. You can edit it per listener from Server Control page.
name: Users.Session.clientCertSsh

description: Shows if password authentication is enabled as a user authentication method on the SSH server. Possible values: <default|disabled>.
name: Users.Session.clientPassSsh

description: Session timeout.
name: Users.Session.idleTimeout

description: Maximum failed login attempts <n>.
name: Users.Session.maxAuthAttempts

description: Control SSL session <optional|required> <class>.
name: Users.SslEncryption

description: It specifies bandwidth statistics interval value in seconds.
name: Users.Statistics.BandwidthInterval

description: It specifies a time interval for statistic (Session and Bandwidth) snapshot invalidation period.
name: Users.Statistics.InvalidationInterval

description: It specifies statistics snapshot time to live value in seconds, used for keeping a snapshot in case of network latency during transfer of large statistics snapshots.
name: Users.Statistics.SnapshotTTL

description: Upload restrictions <yes|no> <class> <path> [{user|uid} {group|gid} [mode]].
name: Users.Uploads

description: Controls the degree of upload restrictions application. If set to "limited" - the upload restriction configuration will be ignored in case the file mode is set by the client. If set to "full" - the upload restriction configuration will be applied regardless of the file mode set by the client. Available values: limited | full
name: Users.Uploads.RestrictionsApplication

description: Virtual groups <group|gid>.
name: Users.VirtualGroups

description: Enables or disables Basic authentication method for Admin REST API. Possible values - true|false
name: Webservices.Admin.BasicAuthEnabled

description: Specify the certificate alias used for encryption/decryption of protected objects for the Admin REST services when it is set. Possible values -  empty or alias of used certificate.
name: Webservices.Admin.CertAlias

description: Enables CSRF token protection for Admin Web services. It can be specified on what header CSRF token protection is based. It can be specified if Referer header based protection is preserved or not when CSRF token protection is enabled. Possible values are true | false. The default one is false.
name: Webservices.Admin.CsrfToken.enabled

description: Contains regular expression describing Host header white-list for Admin web services.
name: Webservices.Admin.Host.Whitelist

description: Maximum Transfers to be resubmitted at once.
name: Webservices.Admin.MaxResubmits

description: Contains regular expression describing Referer header white-list for Admin API web services.
name: Webservices.Admin.Referer.Whitelist

description: Defines the  number of entries shown per page when displaying a list of entries.
name: Webservices.EntriesPerPage

description: Enables CSRF token protection for HTTP Web services. It can be specified on what header CSRF token protection is based. It can be specified if Referer header based protection is preserved or not when CSRF token protection is enabled. Possible values are true | false. The default one is false.
name: Webservices.Http.CsrfToken.enabled

description: Contains regular expression describing Host header white-list for Public web services.
name: Webservices.Public.Host.Whitelist

description: Contains regular expression describing Referer header white-list for Public API web services.
name: Webservices.Public.Referer.Whitelist

description: When this option is enabled, SecureTransport creates a log entry for the zero-byte transfer where the name of the file is the download pattern. When disabled, the application does not log zero-byte transfers. The option is not applicable for Pluggable Transfer Sites and Folder Monitor.
name: ZeroByteWildcardPullAllowed
